================
description
================

1) This program accept file name and any string from user and open that file in default mode(Write).
2) after open gets successful it will write the given "word" into that file
3) Required filename and "word" will be taken from command line

================
about the code
================

	input	:	file_name, word
	output	:	result - file descripter
 			
=============
How to run
=============

	make	:	compile the code and generates executable file as "myexe"
	make run:	run the executable with command line argument
			for this you have to pass parameter as: 
			
			$ make run p1="parameter_value1" p2="parameter_value2"
	
=============
NOTE
=============

	1)If the given file is unable to open, it will display the appropriate reason.
	2)If given file is not present in the working directory, it creates new file with the given name.
	and write the data into that file.
